  "aboutText": "The Golden Pothos is the archetypal beginner houseplant, prized for its trailing vines of heart-shaped leaves splashed with irregular yellow variegation. In the wild it climbs rainforest trunks as a hemiepiphyte, its juvenile leaves staying small until it finds something to scale, at which point the foliage enlarges dramatically. Its tolerance of low light, irregular watering, and general neglect has made it a fixture of offices and homes across the globe. Propagation is famously easy from stem cuttings rooted in water, which has helped cement its status as the plant most people grow first.",
